name_title: Formula X Brilliants
description: What it is:Formula X Brilliant is a dazzling and vibrant glitter lacquer with intense sparkle.What it does:Far from your regular color, this multidimensional minx nail lacquer delivers the ultimate in disco ball sparkle. - Multicolored twinkling glitter makes a daring statement in just one swipeWhat it is formulated WITHOUT:- ParabensWhat else you need to know:The brush design was engineered to complement the highly pigmented, three-free formula, giving you the most even and precise lacquer application. Size0.4 oz
Reviews: [{'User': 'asfi3222', 'Review': 'I gave this 3 stars ONLY because the color is truly amazing. Otherwise Id give it only 1 star based on lack of longevity. It is so shiny and sparkly, but it flakes off in very large pieces after less than a day of wearing. The photo was taken just a few hours after finishing my nails and I didnt do anything strenuous that would excuse my nails chipping so quickly, but all of the polish on my index finger was gone, and most of my thumb as well. I always use base and top coat and manicures usually last me a week, sometimes more with minimal chipping and wear. I was very disappointed with how easily it chips off compared to other brands. I bought 7 different colors from this brand so I hope that it is just a texture thing with the Brilliants line and that the entire line doesnt chip so easily! Ill still keep it because the color is so beautiful.', 'Score': 1, 'user_data': {'dob': '1977-08-01 00:00:00', 'state': 'California', 'age': 41, 'statecode': 'CA'}}, {'User': 'nomk2422', 'Review': 'At this point Ive purchased 26 Formula X nail polishes in various formulas and I love them all! They last longer than any nail polishes Ive ever used in my life, and Ive tried a boat load. Before Formula X nail polishes everything I ever tried would chip within a day or two on my natural nails. Now only paint my nails once a week and Im a very active person who isnt easy on her nails and hands. The key for longevity & anti-chip wear is you MUST use the Formula X top & base coat which are formulated for the nail polish. No other brands compare to Formula X top & base coat, Ive tried them all! name_title: Foreo Luna™ For Combination Skin
description: What it is:A silicone facial brush for combination skin that channels both T-sonic pulsations for deep and gentle cleansing, and lower-frequency pulsations to reduce the signs of aging. What it does: The LUNA for Combination Skin’s brush surface features up to 80 percent of thinner silicone touch-points for gentle cleansing, with two additional waves of thicker touch-points for cleansing oily patches. The antiaging surface on the reverse side consists of a series of concentric silicone waves. The LUNA reduces the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles and leaves the skin looking and feeling firmer and more elastic. It removes dead skin cells and unclogs pores of dirt, oil, and makeup residue, while enhancing the absorption of the client's favorite skincare products. What else you need to know:This facial brush is phthalate-free and uses body-safe silicone. It comes with a charger and a two-year warranty. "FOREO is revolutionizing the beauty world."Vogue Suggested Usage:-Use for two minutes twice daily with any cleanser, with the exception of clay-based, silicone-based, or grainy cleansers, exfoliators, or scrubs. -To use, turn on, apply cleanser, wet brush surface, and cleanse face and rinse. -After, apply the antiaging surface to wrinkle-prone areas. Precautions:-Anyone who suffers from a serious skin condition should consult their dermatologist before using the LUNA. -Clay-based, silicone-based, or grainy cleansers, exfoliators, or scrubs should be avoided, as they may harm the LUNA's soft silicone touch-points.
Reviews: [{'User': 'qopf2344', 'Review': 'I went on a 3-week business trip recently and didnt take my new Luna with me. My skin never really felt totally clean unless I exfoliated or kept a mask on my face for 30 minutes, and my makeup didnt go on as smoothly.', 'Score': 2, 'user_data': {'dob': '1973-08-02 00:00:00', 'state': 'Wisconsin', 'age': 45, 'statecode': 'WI'}}, {'User': 'buuo4341', 'Review': 'Long story short, in under 5 minutes a day this little thing made a HUGE difference in my skin. Its the kind of thing that you dont realize how much it does for you until you dont have it anymore, and I never want to leave mine behind again!', 'Score': 2, 'user_data': {'dob': '1985-07-30 00:00:00', 'state': 'Puerto Rico', 'age': 33, 'statecode': 'PR'}}, {'User': 'aaoj3233', 'Review': 'my clarisonic mia finally died on me so i decided to give the luna a try, since its new and seems interesting. its only been 1 day but i love the luna so much! it feels gentle during cleansing but makes my skin very smooth and soft. i prefer this over the clarisonic because its not as harsh, can reach difficult places like the sides of my nose, and cleans deeper. with the clarisonic (mia) i could still feel blackheads and clogged pores but not with the luna.', 'Score': 2, 'user_data': {'dob': '1951-08-08 00:00:00', 'state': 'California', 'age': 67, 'statecode': 'CA'}}, {'User': 'vwuj3242', 'Review': 'i do sometimes miss the exfoliating of the clarisonic but that can be replaced with a good exfoliating scrub that i always have anyway.', 'Score': 1, 'user_data': {'dob': '1981-07-31 00:00:00', 'state': 'American Samoa', 'age': 37, 'statecode': 'AS'}}, {'User': 'mlqt3134', 'Review': 'tip: dont keep it for too long on the sides of your nose because although youre cleaning out the clogged pores, it will make the skin around your nose very red and irritated.', 'Score': 2, 'user_data': {'dob': '1981-07-31 00:00:00', 'state': 'Idaho', 'age': 37, 'statecode': 'ID'}}, {'User': 'ijch4444', 'Review': 'i wondered a lot if i should get the luna or luna mini? definitely the full size luna. it fits perfectly in my hand and any smaller would be uncontrollable and too small. the difference in price is worth it.', 'Score': 3, 'user_data': {'dob': '1973-08-02 00:00:00', 'state': 'Illinois', 'age': 45, 'statecode': 'IL'}}, {'User': 'appf4231', 'Review': 'I was a clarisonic user for a good couple of years when my skin was extremely oily with acne. I stopped using the clarisonic because it became too abrasive and I was spending so much money constantly changing the brush heads. I had read about Foreo when it first came out and tried the Luna Mini since it was cheaper. I didnt love it and returned it after a few uses because it made no difference in my skin. A year later which was a few weeks ago, sephora had a sale which sold this Luna combination in with Boscia cleansers for $169. It was a great deal so I bit the bullet and purchased it. I have absolutely NO regrets. The full sized foreo is AMAZING and my skin has been so soft ever since using it. For someone who is acne prone and have always had congested pores, the foreo is a godsend. I could have never thought such soft silicone bristles could cleanse so thoroughly. The foreo knocks clarisonic out of the park and is cheaper in the long run. If you have been interested in trying this, go buy it now! It will change your skin!', 'Score': 1, 'user_data': {'dob': '1980-07-31 00:00:00', 'state': 'New Hampshire', 'age': 38, 'statecode': 'NH'}}, {'User': 'fblv1324', 'Review': 'I finally gave in and bought the Luna for myself after months of debating whether or not to buy one. So glad I just went and did it. This is the best skin care investment I have ever made. Ive only been using it for a week now and my skin has already changed dramatically. I always have small pimples and blackheads all over my chin, and no matter what I did, I couldnt get them to go away. You could see all the bumps through every kind of foundation. After just 3 days of using the Luna my chin has cleared up. Nothing has every made my chin so smooth. My larger pores on my cheeks are gone. The blackheads on my nose are almost completely gone. This little tool is amazing. You can feel how clean and smooth is makes your skin just after the first use. I highly suggest giving it a try before spending 100s on face products. This is the only expensive face care product you need.', 'Score': 3, 'user_data': {'dob': '1982-07-31 00:00:00', 'state': 'Alaska', 'age': 36, 'statecode': 'AK'}}, {'User': 'aqoa3443', 'Review': 'I notice that there are drastic differences between peoples comments about this product. I understand that people will either like it or hate it because it does not seem incredibly amazing upon your first use. However, as I tried clarisonic before and comparing to this, this is less harsh and more gentle to my skin while being able to clear my pore and I can still use it everyday, It feels good using it as it vibrates my skin and I can feel the dirt being wipped off(i know it sounds a bit exaggerated). Regardless, this is a good value to get it rather than the clarisonic ones because you do not have to buy brush heads all the time and at least it works on my skin! I might exchange it for a foreo luna mini though because I am just 18 and I feel like the anti-aging function is not really necessary. For some reason I couldnt make the investment. Im glad I waited until I saw this product as an alternative.After three days, I noticed more even skin tone with some of the dullness abating. I used a biore strip to investigate and sure enough it came back as clean as I had ever seen it.Its lasted almost two months on the initial charge and the alerts make it easy to use. As for the anti aging side, Im not sure if its effective or just a placebo but I did notice my laugh lines are less prominent. description: What it is: A set of five eye brushes and a volumizing mascara designed for stunning smoky eyes. name_title: St. John's Bay® Long-Sleeve Cable Crewneck Sweater
description: Our classic cable knit sweater gets a casual update with a flatteringly comfortable fit. cotton/nylon machine wash cold inside out, lay flat to dry imported
Reviews: [{'User': 'tqah2324', 'Review': 'These are wonderful. Theyre cozy cotton sweaters in pleasant colors, and they last. I bought about six last winter and wore them almost constantly all season, to find that when I tried one on today it still fits perfectly and is snuggly-warm.', 'Score': 3, 'user_data': {'dob': '1999-07-27 00:00:00', 'state': 'Connecticut', 'age': 19, 'statecode': 'CT'}}, {'User': 'wlgx4132', 'Review': 'Also, the color stays. I cant guarantee they wont bleed on other clothes a little the first time you wash them (I dont remember), but they stay really vibrant even after a season of wear, which probably means the color is going nowhere in the seasons to come too.', 'Score': 2, 'user_data': {'dob': '1971-08-03 00:00:00', 'state': 'Colorado', 'age': 47, 'statecode': 'CO'}}, {'User': 'yfpo4432', 'Review': 'A few tips:1) Go into the store to try one on. The first one I tried on was a size too small--both physically uncomfortable and a one-way ticket to self-consciousness--but one size up and it was cute and comfortable. It was as if Id picked up an entirely different brand. If youre going to buy these, at the very least get some recent and accurate measurements and compare them to the chart.', 'Score': 4, 'user_data': {'dob': '1958-08-06 00:00:00', 'state': 'Wyoming', 'age': 60, 'statecode': 'WY'}}, {'User': 'bxpl4324', 'Review': 'XL fits perfectly on me; Im 55 and bust-waist-hips is 45-39-48, and you can see how long the sweater comes to my hips in my picture. Hope this helps my fellow curvy girls!', 'Score': 2, 'user_data': {'dob': '1953-08-07 00:00:00', 'state': 'Nebraska', 'age': 65, 'statecode': 'NE'}}, {'User': 'ctuz2113', 'Review': '2) You can wash them along with other clothes--they arent picky there--but youll want to dry them by hanging or laying them flat most of the time. Occasionally run them through the dryer if the fit starts feeling odd (which can happen if you hang them to dry, as they start to stretch lengthwise).', 'Score': 3, 'user_data': {'dob': '1979-08-01 00:00:00', 'state': 'Georgia', 'age': 39, 'statecode': 'GA'}}, {'User': 'przu2241', 'Review': 'Its best if, when you use the dryer, you hang around when its about to finish and put your sweater on as soon as you can after it comes out... not because itll dry better or anything, but because its really warm and it feels absolutely luxurious. :)', 'Score': 3, 'user_data': {'dob': '1988-07-29 00:00:00', 'state': 'District of Columbia', 'age': 30, 'statecode': 'DC'}}, {'User': 'vycc3341', 'Review': 'I bought this sweater with the intention of wearing it when I travel to places with a cold climate, but, even though, it is pretty, soft and comfortable, it is way too short in length for me. I am 58 and it comes to the top of my hips, so I gave it to my mother who is 51 and it fit her beautifully. It was also a bit big on me, I am a Regular Size 4 and big chested and the Small would have been a better fit for me. My mom is Size 8 Petite and the Medium was perfect for her.', 'Score': 4, 'user_data': {'dob': '1971-08-03 00:00:00', 'state': 'Kansas', 'age': 47, 'statecode': 'KS'}}, {'User': 'qkqm2413', 'Review': 'Pleasantly surprised by the lush quality and bouncy texture of this sweater, I bought in several different colors before seasons end. Wear layered over tees and tanks on cold days, wear over a cami on warmer days. Dress it up with an infinity scarf or statement necklace. Washes well as directed on label, minimal shrinkage if washed in cold water and line dried. Otherwise, this sweater quickly became my seasonal favorite for work and play!', 'Score': 1, 'user_data': {'dob': '1954-08-07 00:00:00', 'state': 'Alabama', 'age': 64, 'statecode': 'AL'}}, {'User': 'ysfz3143', 'Review': 'I have several of these in different colors. name_title: JCPenney Home™ Cotton Duck Thermal Roman Shade
description: Our cotton duck thermal roman shade is the perfect, stylish solution for reducing energy costs.   100% cotton duck fabric is backed with insulating thermal acrylic foam unique design folds neatly as shade is raised auto-locking pull cord protect your home from the heat and cold white backing faces outside for uniform exterior appearance optional 7" valance Sold individually. Cotton. Window must be at least 1" deep for inside mount; 1¾" deep for flush inside mount. Mounting hardware included. Vacuum or dust. Imported.  *Cost savings represent the relative cost of heating or cooling an area to account for heat lost or gained through a window. Savings reflect comparison to a bare single-pane window. Energy Savings logo developed by JCPenney for exclusive use. Energy Savings testing conducted by an independent third-party laboratory.

name_title: James Read Express Bronzing Mousse
description: What it is:A conditioning, non-aerosol mousse that creates a light golden glow in just one hour, a medium tan in two hours, and a deep bronze shade after three hours. What it is formulated to do:This revolutionary fast-acting mousse with bronze control technology allows you to pick your desired shade of tanensuring easy application and a flawless finish every time. Great for use on the face and body, the odorless formula deliver a golden glow in as little as one hour, a medium shade tan in two, and a deeper, darker bronze shade after just three hours. What it is formulated without:- Parabens- Sulfates- PhthalatesWhat else you need to know:This product is fragrance-free.Suggested Usage:-Exfoliate and moisturize thoroughly prior to application.-Apply to the body in circular motions using the James Read Tanning Mitt, working in sections. -Ensure the product has been applied all over; leave feet and hands until last using what remains on the mitt. -Wait until skin is touch dry before dressing and avoid contact with water for at least 60 minutes. -Suitable for use on face and body. -For optimal results, moisturize daily and exfoliate regularly to ensure an even tone. Precautions:-A patch test is recommended at least 24 hours prior to use. -If there are any adverse reactions, discontinue to use. -Do not apply to broken, irritated, or sensitive skin. -Stop using if your skin becomes irritated. -Wash palms thoroughly immediately after use if not using a tanning mitt. -Self-tanner may stain, so take care not to get it on furnishings, fabric, paintwork, or light hair. -Avoid getting it into your eyes; if you do, simply rinse thoroughly with water. -Avoid contact with lips. -For external use only. -Sun safety warning: this product does not contain a sunscreen and does not protect against sunburn. Repeated exposure of unprotected skin while tanning may increase the risk of skin aging, skin cancer and other harmful effects to the skin even if you do not burn. Size:6.7 ozIngredients:​ -Witch Hazel Extract and Cucumber Extract: Tone the skin. -Pomegranate Extract, Horse Chestnut Extract, and Vitamin E: Act as tan accelerators. Water, Dihydroxyacetone, Propylene Glycol, Glycerin, Ethoxydiglycol, Aloe Barbadensis (Aloe Vera Leaf Juice) , Sodium C14-16 Olefin Sulfonate, Phenoxyethanol, Sodium Benzoate, Erythrulose, Tocopherol (Vitamin E), Retinyl Palmitate (Vitamin A), Ubiquinone (CQ10), Camellia Sinensis (Green Tea Extract), CI 16035,CI 19140, CI42090.

name_title: Urban Decay Naked2
description: What it is: The most anticipated sequel of the decade, Naked2 features a dozen pigment-rich taupe and gray-beige neutrals, plus five exclusive, new shades. What it does: The follow up to the original bestselling Naked palette, this stunning second edition proves that neutral is anything but boring. Showcasing a dozen completely different shades than the first bronze-based collection, it includes a stunning range from pale and deep, to matte and sparkly. You'll achieve a host of new neutral looks, smoky dramatic eyes, and everything in between. The palette also includes a double-ended, cruelty-free Good Karma Shadow/Crease Brush (available only in this palette), and four sample packettes of Eyeshadow Primer Potion. This set contains: - 12 x 0.05 oz Eyeshadows in Foxy (cream bisque with matte finish), Half Baked (golden-bronze with shimmering finish), Booty Call (shimmering cork), Chopper (copper shimmer with silver microglitter), Tease (creamy pale brown with matte finish), Snake Bite (dark bronze shimmer with metallic base), Suspect (pale golden beige with shimmering finish), Pistol (light gray-brown with shimmering finish), Verve (oyster with shimmering finish), YDK (cool bronze shimmer with metallic base), Busted (deep brown with shimmering finish), Blackout (blackest black with matte finish) - Good Karma Shadow/Crease Brush - 4 x 0.025 oz Eyeshadow Primer Potion sample packettes What else you need to know: Urban Decay's packaging takes on a modern feel in Naked2. With an art-school-inspired tin case and a hinged lid, it's smooth and cool to the touch. Compare Naked2 with first Naked palette—packaged in warm, rich brown velvet with gold foil lettering—and you won't be able to resist owning both. The eye shadows in this palette coordinate with the 24/7 Glide-On Double-Ended Eye Pencil: Perversion (blackest-black matte)/Pistol (light gray-brown shimmer).

name_title: Samsung ENERGY STAR® 23 cu. ft. 36” Wide French Door Counter Depth Refrigerator with water and Ice Dispenser
description: true This counter depth French-door refrigerator from Samsung blends in with your cabinetry, adding function and style to your kitchen. ENERGY STAR® qualified external water and ice dispenser Ice Master ice maker in refrigerator saves room and makes up to 5.2 lbs. of ice per day and stores nearly 2.7 lbs. water filter: HAF-CIN/EXP control panel features digital display and temperature control Twin Cooling Plus™ cools refrigerator and freezer compartments independently to help produce stay fresher, longer and reduce the chances of freezer burn 5 tempered glass spill-proof shelves 1 full-width CoolSelect Pantry™ with separate temperature control 2 humidity-controlled crispers 6 three-gallon door bins 6.8 cu. ft. freezer capacity EZ-Open™ handle allows for easy opening and closing of a fully loaded freezer 22 cu. ft. capacity counter depth design allows for more workable space in the kitchen high-efficiency LED lighting delivers brighter, cooler and more energy-efficient lighting alarm alerts you when any refrigerator door is open more than 3 minutes available in black, white or stainless steel 3-door French door counter depth refrigerator with 2 fresh food doors, one freezer door and external ice and water dispenser

name_title: Marc Jacobs Beauty Enamored Hi-Shine Nail Polish
description: What it is:A superior nail polish with unprecedented finish and a shine like that goes on like 30 coats of lacquer. What it does:Coat nails with this fresh take on nail polish. Inspired by Marc’s highly lacquered coffee table, Enamored Hi-Shine Nail Polish is formulated with patented bonding agents that deliver a plasticized, wet look while the color rich creams and fine glitters ensure vivid, chip-resistant color. These shades are inspired by Marc’s favorite movies. What else you need to know: The curvature of the bottle resembles a smile, and the custom, curve-hugging brush optimizes application. "Shiny is my favorite color"Marc JacobsSize:0.43 oz
Reviews: [{'User': 'cqzm1433', 'Review': 'I bought this polish in Petra and was so impressed that I went back for two more colors. Petra was fully opaque in one coat, which was fantastic. The others took two coats, which was fine. I dont know if it really has the shine of 30 coats of polish, but since I used a glossy top coat it didnt really matter. What I loved was that the application was a dream. The polish went on evenly with zero smudges or streaks. With each of them I was able to get a week of wear before I even saw any tip wear and minor chipping. I usually change my polish every 2-3 days, but the colors were so amazing and the wear so great that I didnt really want to remove it. I did use a good base coat and top coat which probably helped. I took away one star only because Id like to see more unique colors. Petra was super-unique but Id love to see some multi-chromes or linear holos in the lineup.', 'Score': 5, 'user_data': {'dob': '1987-07-30 00:00:00', 'state': 'Guam', 'age': 31, 'statecode': 'GU'}}, {'User': 'vsqn3242', 'Review': 'I thought sally was going to be a bit more greener but it more of a black. It started in September when I ordered the old Keurig system, because I had heard too many negatives about the 2.0. Well, the old one, a K45, didnt work well at all. I complained and Keurig sent the K2.0 350 as a replacement. No better! They sent out a K2.0 300. It was the same. Took way over 2 minutes to brew a cup. In the meantime, as I am complaining to family and friends about the lengthy brew time, they informed me, three of them, that the K2.0 200 worked like a charm and delivered coffee quickly! As I called again about the horrible performance of the K2.0 300, Keurig graciously offered to upgrade to the more expensive model. I immediately said No, just send me the cheaper one, the K2.0 200, because I know this one has a good track record. This model works the best! Believe me!!! Fast brewing (50 seconds), hot, and you can use your own coffee pod to brew your own brand without using the expensive Kcups, if that is what you want to do!! It took me 4 Keurigs to finally get one that delivers. This one is finally a keeper!!!', 'Score': 3, 'user_data': {'dob': '1970-08-03 00:00:00', 'state': 'West Virginia', 'age': 48, 'statecode': 'WV'}}, {'User': 'rjxp1322', 'Review': 'Received this product as a gift. After years of using my old Keurig Mini , I was excited to get the new 2.0. Bottom line, I went back to using my old keurig mini after about 2 weeks. Nothing I do removes the burnt plastic taste from my coffee. I have soaked all removable parts (water reservoir, k-cup holder, etc) in white vineagar over night, spent an hour running white vinegar and water cleanses through the machine, and I even washed all the removable parts in the dishwasher (something youre not supposed to do but it was my last resort). Nothing I do removes the plastic taste and smell. Everything I try to brew is undrinkable. Reading the reviews from other 2.0 owners, I see I am not the only one drinking coffee that tastes like a burnt barbie doll. I have been a loyal customer for years, and even recruited my parents to the brand (my mom owns a coffee shop so this was quiet a feat), but I am now fearful of the plastic being used in the new 2.0 brewers. This will probably be the last Keurig product I use.', 'Score': 2, 'user_data': {'dob': '1992-07-28 00:00:00', 'state': 'Maine', 'age': 26, 'statecode': 'ME'}}, {'User': 'qufh1314', 'Review': 'I bought the Keurig to replace my coffee maker of a different brand. I was familiar with Keurigs however because weve always had one at work. First thing I realized: there arent 9 sizes as advertised! I was excited about making a larger cup of coffee... but no go. Second the machine is loud. Why? And since I can only make a 10oz cup, why do I have to put so much water into the water reservoir? Lastly, whats the deal with the filter that is in the package, but mentioned no where in the instructions? So weird and incomplete. My coffee was good, but for the money, I want a product that was advertised and as good as the older models Ive used in the past at work. Im taking my K200 back.', 'Score': 3, 'user_data': {'dob': '1952-08-07 00:00:00', 'state': 'Colorado', 'age': 66, 'statecode': 'CO'}}, {'User': 'appf4231', 'Review': 'even though some pods are labeled for use. such as Meijer brand. machine clogs up and coffee grounds go all over machine inside. went through 3 machines in 3 weeks. still not right. tech support even said that our filtered water was too clean. we replaced a 10+year old bun coffee maker that still works. thought this would be more convenient. we like the variety of pods. just wish that if it says keurig brewed on package. it would work properly.', 'Score': 1, 'user_data': {'dob': '1980-07-31 00:00:00', 'state': 'New Hampshire', 'age': 38, 'statecode': 'NH'}}, {'User': 'zsej1424', 'Review': 'It takes a lot to get me upset in the morning when I wake up. So i had to disconnect the new 2.0 and put in my old Keurig Elite B45 Brewer which accepts all types of reusable filters. I am on a fixed income and cannot afford to buy a specific filter or buy the Keurig brand K-cups. so most likely I will return this 2.0 ! As I stated before I love my coffee more than a machine to make it !!! Yes I like the touch screen and yes I like the compact design. I also like the fact that I can add a carafe as well and I am upset that I will not be able to enjoy these amenities ! I was really excited and was brimming with anticipation to use this Keurig 2.0 K200 ! And now with one issue(reusable filter),my hopes were shattered, and my morning ruined ! description: true From its sleek exterior, to the cleaning power within, this top control dishwasher is a great enhancement to any kitchen. In addition to the stainless steel tub, this dishwasher features our heavy-duty StormWash cleaning system, a hard food dispenser, and an adjustable racking system that lets you fit just about anything into it. ENERGY STAR® qualified top and front display with electronic touch sensor stainless steel tub 2 adjustable racks make it easy to load different size dishes StormWash™ - This heavy-duty wash system delivers powerful washing for your toughest dishes. Enjoy powerful, efficient dishwashing in peace with a special insulation system that significantly reduces noise to 46 dBA Adjustable racking system - Clean even your tallest and most oversized items with ease with a flexible and easy to use design that allows for more space on the top rack Half load cycle lets you wash small loads while maximizing effectiveness with this feature, saving energy and water. name_title: Too Faced 3 - Way Lash Lining Tool
description: What it is: A triple-tip lash emphasizing tool for thicker looking lashes, smoother tight lining, and better eye lining.What it does:This innovative lash tool lets you become your own lash expert. The triple tip delivers ultra-black liner between lashes to fill spaces between lashes so that the lash line appears thicker, instantly. Fine points make it easy to define along the root of the lash line, for a more dramatic lash look. Three felt tips strategically line eyes with a more steady, smooth line, and all lines use a rich triple black coating to give a full, more even application. It’s great for creating the perfect cat eye.What it is formulated WITHOUT:- Synthetic Dyes- PetrochemicalsWhat else you need to know:This long-wearing product is color rich, carbon black-based, dries quickly, and can be removed with warm water and cleanser. It does not contain fragrance.Suggested Usage:-For lush lashes: Dot between lashes to boost the appearance of lash thickness.-For a classic liquid liner application, press the prongs along the lash line until the line is solid.-Stay close to the roots for a narrow line and repeat until you attain the desired thickness. It’s so easy and mistake proof.-For a dramatic cat eye: After drawing a thin line across the base of your lashes, extend the line past your eye with a gentle flick of the wrist. You can go back and make the line thicker or darker, as desired.Size:0.02 ozIngredients​Water, Acrylates Copolymer, Glycerin, Alcohol Denat., Propanediol, Laureth-21, PEG-40 Hydrogenated Castor Oil, PEG-60 Hydrogenated Castor Oil, Sodium Dehydroacetate, 1,2-Hexanediol, Ethylhexylglycerin, Arginine, Disodium EDTA, Caprylyl Glycol, Phenoxyethanol, Methylparaben, Black 2 (CI 77266).

Reviews: [{'User': 'bsgi1144', 'Review': 'I ordered these for a bedroom because I needed blackout quality and wanted some insulating properties. I ordered the gold color, 6 panels 95 inch size, including a couple extra panels in case there was a great disparity in lengths or stack back (fullness), but just returned the extra two as not needed. name_title: Urban Decay Naked Skin Color Correcting Fluid
description: What it is: A collection of high-tech, color-correcting formulas that blur the look of imperfections. What it does: Correct imperfections and play up your best features, all without having to lug around a whole contour kit. With five color-neutralizing shades to target every skin concern, Urban Decay’s Naked Skin Color Correcting Fluid features an innovative, lightweight formula that instantly color-corrects and blurs flaws, leaving skin illuminated and bright. Subtle pearlescent pigments diffuse light to perfect skin, while antioxidant-rich vitamins C and E condition and protect. Unlike a lot of cream-based color correctors, this liquid formula is easy to use and always blends flawlessly for a smooth, even application. What it is formulated WITHOUT: - Parabens - Sulfates - Phthalates What else you need to know: You can see the shade through the clear bottle, so it’s easy to find the right one in your bag. No need to carry a brush either; the modern flocked applicator picks up and lays down just the right amount of product. And it’s soft enough to use on the delicate skin under the eyes. Choose the shade that targets your skin concerns: Green reduces redness. Lavender balances sallowness. Pink brightens dark areas. Yellow corrects dullness. Peach masks circles/spots.Ingredients:Water, Cyclopentasiloxane, C12-15 Alkyl Benzoate, Glycerin, Butylene Glycol, Methyl Methacrylate Crosspolymer, PEG-10 Dimethicone, Dimethicone, Dimethicone/PEG-10/15 Crosspolymer, Phenoxyethanol, Acrylates/Dimethicone Copolymer, Boron Nitride, Lecithin, Magnesium Sulfate, Nylon-12, Disodium Stearoyl Glutamate, Caprylyl Glycol, Lauroyl Lysine, Tocopheryl Acetate, Hexylene Glycol, Aluminum Hydroxide, Ascorbyl Glucoside, Dipropylene Glycol, Sodium Citrate, Steareth-20, Sodium Hyaluronate, Tocopherol, Chlorhexidine Digluconate, N-Hydroxysuccinimide, Potassium Sorbate, Chrysin, Palmitoyl Tripeptide-1, Palmitoyl Tetrapeptide-7. [+/- (All Shades May Contain: Mica, CI 77891 (Titanium Dioxide), CI 77491/77492/77499 (Iron Oxides), CI 77007 (Ultramarines), CI 77288 (Chromium Oxide Greens)].

name_title: MAKE UP FOR EVER 270 Angled Eyebrow Brush
description: What it is:A short, firm, angled brush used to fill in the eyebrows.What it does:This brush is ideal for filling in eyebrows or precise blending of brow pencils for a natural look. It is firm and features straight fibers, which can be used to create dotted effects. The fine tip can even be used to draw individual eyebrow hairs. It can be used with creams, pencils, and compact powders.What else you need to know:After five years in development with makeup artists and fiber experts, MAKE UP FOR EVER Artisan Brushes are a revolution in brush craftsmanship. The 100-percent fiber brushes are available in a range of 76 handcrafted styles, each with the perfect balance of straight and wavy fibers that replicate natural hairs. Beveled tips create a two-in-one makeup brush and tool, while innovative hair density and brush head shapes optimize every stroke for ideal makeup application. To achieve the ultimate collection, every brush has gone through 25 production stages by 30 craftsmen and has been checked for quality 50 times.Ingredients-Brown Algae Extract: Hydrates soothes, and reduces redness.Mica, Isododecane, Isohexadecane, Cyclopentasiloxane, Silica, C13-15 Alkane, Octyldodecanol, Isopropyl Palmitate, Ricinus Communis (Castor) Seed Oil, C30-45 Alkyl Cetearyl Dimethicone Crosspolymer, Boron Nitride, Dimethicone/ Vinyltrimethylsiloxysilicate Crosspolymer, Lauroyl Lysine, Alaria Esculenta Extract, Ascorbyl Glucoside, Tocotrienols, Tocopherol, Beta-Sitosterol, Elaeis Guineensis (Palm) Oil, Caprylic/Capric Triglyceride, Squalene, Caprylyl Methicone, Flavor (Aroma), Propylene Carbonate, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Potassium Sorbate, Phenoxyethanol, Caprylyl Glycol, Ethylhexylglycerin, Hexylene Glycol. May Contain [+/-]: Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Iron Oxides (CI 77491, 77492, 77499), Red 30 Lake (CI 73360), Yellow 5 Lake (CI 19140 :1).

name_title: GE Profile™ 1.9 Cu. Ft. Over-the-Range Microwave Oven With Sensor Cook Technology
description: true Prepare and heat your meals to perfection every time with this microwave oven with sensor cooking controls that automatically adjusts time and power. A steam cook button also lets you make your steamed favorites. 1.9 cu. ft. capacity 1000 Watts 4-speed, 400-CFM venting fan system quickly removes smoke, steam and odors sensor cooking controls automatically adjusts time and power USDA MyPlate menu offers healthy pre-programmed food options and recipes four-speed with boost recessed turntable with on/off removable oven rack cooktop lighting with three brightness settings
Reviews: [{'User': 'tbps2342', 'Review': 'We bought a new GE Profile Microwave Oven to replace a previous 10-year-old model which had developed arcing in its motor. I am concerned because the newer model has more plastic in its front, top and side construction than its predecessor, which had more stainless steel. And, when you close the door, it feels more lightweight and less solid as its predecessor. But, it seems to measure up, feature wise. There are a few more choices, such as Soften for butter. And, the fan will now go on automatically if too much heat is generated by the stove top beneath. Because of a design change re: the fan (the previous one opened up to release the air; this one has vents in the stationary top), it had to project a bit more forward in the cabinetry, which involved installing it with a sham behind it to push it forward more. There is a monogram on the oven that is not flush, but sticks out. I think that will be a real grease catcher; I wish it had been printed on the panel, instead, like the previous model.', 'Score': 3, 'user_data': {'dob': '1970-08-03 00:00:00', 'state': 'South Dakota', 'age': 48, 'statecode': 'SD'}}, {'User': 'drcq1432', 'Review': 'No need to compromise on this Microwave. I had purchased a Maytag a little over a year ago that look good because it was stainless steel on the inside and outside, but it did not perform well at all. Additionally, it started breaking down within a week of the warranty expiring. The vent fan on the Maytag would blow the flames from the gas stove everywhere making it virtually impossible to cook things while having the vent on. It also did not heat the plates evenly.', 'Score': 1, 'user_data': {'dob': '1953-08-07 00:00:00', 'state': 'Iowa', 'age': 65, 'statecode': 'IA'}}, {'User': 'vduw1322', 'Review': 'This GE Microwave has since solved all of the problems that I have had with the Maytag. It not only heats everything evenly, but even heats faster. The vent on full blast effectively removes steams from food being cooked on the stove without disturbing how evenly the flames hit the pots. This microwave is amazing. I hope it proves to be reliable as time goes on though.', 'Score': 1, 'user_data': {'dob': '1984-07-30 00:00:00', 'state': 'Northern Mariana Islands', 'age': 34, 'statecode': 'MP'}}, {'User': 'ntgs3243', 'Review': 'I was very happy with this microwave until it started turning off periodically when we shut the door. Its really too bad.', 'Score': 2, 'user_data': {'dob': '1985-07-30 00:00:00', 'state': 'North Carolina', 'age': 33, 'statecode': 'NC'}}, {'User': 'pxhd4211', 'Review': 'just brought to replace old 25 yr old sharp pluses dark inside - heats fast-nice looking minuses hard to read control board to dark and small should be backlighted- instructions limited and cheap - sounds cheaply made when opening and closing door', 'Score': 4, 'user_data': {'dob': '1999-07-27 00:00:00', 'state': 'Missouri', 'age': 19, 'statecode': 'MO'}}, {'User': 'zgdp2243', 'Review': 'This is the second one weve had installed (the first was defective). description: Control light and privacy with these handsome wood blinds that add refined, functional style to your space. 2" slat size lift cord Sold individually. Wood. Window must be 1¾" deep for inside mount; 3¼" deep for flush inside mount. Mounting hardware included. Dust lightly. Imported.
Reviews: [{'User': 'lcmt4134', 'Review': 'I purchased some faux wood blinds (at another store, I know, what was I thinking!) and I couldnt deal with how cheap they looked. I didnt want to spend a lot of money because I have 10 windows in the open space I needed the blinds for. So I found these online and took a chance. When I got them I loved the look and the color, I got the black walnut. After they were up I was thrilled to see that the cords to open and close them worked smoothly as well as lifting them up and down. I would caution that they are rather slim boards, but for the price they are really nice. I dont notice that unless I am touching it, meaning on the windows they look perfect. Four of the packages that came were the wrong color ... but JCP was very efficient and nice about correcting that issue and had the new blinds out immediately. Now that they are all up I am LOVING the look and am really happy about them. This review is part of a sweepstakes entry, I mean thats what motivated me to write it, but I assure you it would have been the same review if it was not. name_title: Urban Decay Naked Illuminated
description: What it is:A lightweight, baked powder for face and body with a sophisticated, microfine shimmer that instantly leaves skin with an iridescent shimmer. What it does:Dust on Urban Decay’s Naked Illuminated Shimmering Powder for Face and Body to give you a sexy, just-finished flush. Naked Illuminated powder is first baked on a terra cotta disc for 24 hours, and then it is finished by hand. Baking the powder gives it a high level of just-perfect shimmer, without the metallic look of cheaper formulas. This lightweight, baked powder has a sophisticated microfine shimmer that’s smooth and silky, with light-reflecting particles that leave a luminous, radiant look. Formulated to give the color payoff of a loose powder and the convenience of a pressed powder, this shimmering powder comes in a gorgeous box that makes the perfect gift. It features a generous mirror and a brushhoused in a separate compartment underneath the powder. This smooth, silky powder contains light-reflecting particles that create a luminous, radiant look. Simply brush on this powder wherever you want to create an instant glow.Suggested Usage:-Use this powder to highlight from your cheekbones to your collarbone and beyond.Size:0.2 oz

I must say, I made a great decision. I wear these boots for 10-12 hours a day working on construction sites, and my feet feel great at the end of the day. I was a bit skeptical when I took them out of the box, because they are much lighter than my previous pair of work boots. They broke in easily and never rubbed any part of my foot raw or to a blister. The toe area is very roomy. I have feet that are borderline narrow, so finding boots that fit my feet comfortably with out being tightened all the way is a challenge. Time will tell with how much these boots will stretch, but so far after a month of wearing them, I still have room to tighten them more, which is great so I can wear them at a comfortable snugness. They are a 6 category boot, but comparing them to some others that I have had, they are a high 6, which still sits at a good spot on my ankle/leg. The tongue has ample cushioning on the upper, and has stayed centered on my leg (other boots I have had the tongue tends to wander to the side).So far my only complaint has been where the laces transition from the foot to the ankle staying tighter while the toe and upper have been a little loose, and trying to balance that portion out.', 'Score': 1, 'user_data': {'dob': '1985-07-30 00:00:00', 'state': 'Vermont', 'age': 33, 'statecode': 'VT'}}, {'User': 'zxmr4442', 'Review': 'Update July 2015:Six months is usually the test on whether a pair of boots will cut it or need to be tossed. I am glad to say that these boots have made the cut. The leather itself has held up well, even with being in muddy conditions. No cracking or deep creases. There is no signs of separation in any of the seams or soles. They have not stretched out like other boots, so they still fit really nicely. I am still on the first set of laces which is a plus. I have to do a lot of walking on my current job, averaging between 8-10 miles a day. My feet are never sore at the end of the day, while my coworkers complain about their dogs barking. I highly recommend these boots if you are looking for a quality, comfortable pair.', 'Score': 3, 'user_data': {'dob': '1997-07-27 00:00:00', 'state': 'Minor Outlying Islands', 'age': 21, 'statecode': 'UM'}}, {'User': 'uiee4232', 'Review': 'Update December 2015:I have changed my mind. name_title: JCPenney Home™ Blackout Cordless Cellular Shade
description: This cordless blackout cellular shade is perfect for bedrooms and media rooms. cordless product safe for homes with young children and pets stacked honeycomb design traps pockets of air resisting the transfer of heat and cold, giving you more control over your heating and cooling costs 9/16" single cell blackout design shade has white backing  brushed-nickel grommets premium, durable spun-lace fabric provides both insulation and privacy snap-in brackets make installation easy to raise or lower, just hold the bottom rail and position the shade exactly where you want Window opening must be at least 1½" deep for inside mount, 2" deep for flush inside mount. Blind received will be ½" shorter to account for deduction of end caps. If exact size is needed, order a blind ½" larger. Hardware and instructions included; some household tools required. Polyester. Vacuum or dust to clean. Imported. Note: White color takes on more of a pale, light gray tone.
Reviews: [{'User': 'askv3222', 'Review': 'I ordered these at the same time as another slightly more expensive blind with the handle and these ultimately turned out to be much better! The size is exactly what I ordered--the others were about 1/2 inch to long. Definitely black out as I get the AM FL sun and unfortunately traffic lights at night due to HOA tree cutting! Color is perfect tan--other was kind of yellow. Installation was a breeze though I did have an initial issue with the clipping blind to clips but was able to overcome by loosening the screw on the ones that I was having problems with. Someone else commented on having both in their home and comparable however, the others did seem to be wider on the blind but I just couldnt get the fit. I was concerned about the framing and top and bottom rail exposure but matches coloring of blinds perfectly and really doesnt need a valance as the installation fits inside the window with no gap on top and looks quite custom. I gave it a 4 on meets expectations because it would be great to have a clip on the blind to adjust it-- perhaps the manufacturer has clips? I will definitely look into. I highly recommend otherwise so far so good!', 'Score': 2, 'user_data': {'dob': '1955-08-07 00:00:00', 'state': 'Wyoming', 'age': 63, 'statecode': 'WY'}}, {'User': 'biuy4341', 'Review': 'These shades are really nice. I am sure they will help lower our energy bills also. The binding on the necks will stretch during the spin cycle and its doesnt return to its normal shape, so I turn them inside out and wash in a laundry bag, works great. name_title: SEPHORA COLLECTION Colorful Wink-It Felt Liner Waterproof
description: What it is: An intensely pigmented, waterproof felt-tip liquid liner. What it does: Graphic liner looks took runways by storm at NYFW for Fall 2015. These liners can be applied like a traditional liner or used to create a dramatic look. Try drawing on a double wing or applying a single dot of color to your lower lash line for a trendy look that makes a statement. What it is formulated WITHOUT: - Parabens Suggested Usage: -Apply directly to the lash line using the felt tip applicator. Precautions: -If possible, store with the tip down to ensure the ink sits behind the applicator tip and doesn't dry out between uses. -Make sure the cap is closed tightly between uses. Size:0.019 ozIngredients:Water, Ammonium Styrene/Acrylates Copolymer, Butylene Glycol, CI 77266 (Carbon Black 2), Alcohol, Beheneth-30, Acrylates/Octylacrylamide Copolymer, Phenoxyethanol, Methylparaben, Polyglyceryl-3 Disiloxane Dimethicone, Propylparaben, Sodium Hydroxide, Ammonium Hydroxide, Disodium Edta, Phenoxyethanol, Sodium Benzoate.
Reviews: [{'User': 'iiwr2341', 'Review': 'love this kind of eyeliner. It may actually be exactly the same as the Stila and the Kat Von D that come in almost identical packages. Until I bought this I used either one of those interchangably, they all work exactly the same. However, about two weeks after purchasing this, my entire makeup bag was covered in what looked like black and silver glitter. It was the writing on the outside of this eyeliner falling off and getting all over my stuff!! I ran water over the outside and it filled up my whole sink with this glitter. My makeup bag is a mess, every time I pick something up in there I got it all over my hands and face when Id put makeup on. Worst packaging ever. I ended up washing off everything in my bag and wrapping the outside of the tube in shipping tape.This is $7 cheaper than Stila and $5 cheaper than the Kat Von D, but the packaging is awful. If I do buy it again, Ill wrap it in tape immediately!Other than that its great. Works just as well as the others that are so much more. All day liner.', 'Score': 3, 'user_data': {'dob': '1979-08-01 00:00:00', 'state': 'South Dakota', 'age': 39, 'statecode': 'SD'}}, {'User': 'heew2311', 'Review': 'I really like this product. I think it is a cheap alternative to some of the more expensive liquid felt tip eyeliners. Ive bought this in the brown, dark green, and dark blue colours. I love how easy it is to apply. I understand where some of the reviews are saying it can erase the line if you go over it or that it dried out. I find its best if you store it upside down (I use the older Real techniques brushes stand for this) to keep lots of product in the tip. When there is more product on the tip I find it does less of the erasing if you go over the line again. I also found waiting a bit before correcting your line stops the erasing issue. You can correct it if you do it right away but once it sets you may need remover to fix it. Ive never tried to smudge it but it does last long...unless youre like me and forget you have makeup on and rub your eyes then it can flake a bit...otherwise long lasting. The dark green and dark blue can end up looking more like a black or brown if you apply them too much I find. I love this product and will continue to buy it.', 'Score': 1, 'user_data': {'dob': '1969-08-03 00:00:00', 'state': 'Utah', 'age': 49, 'statecode': 'UT'}}, {'User': 'tlfq4423', 'Review': 'It is perfect for the wing liner look and others. Easy to apply and drys quick. So HAPPY with this purchase. Will be a regular purchase of mine.', 'Score': 5, 'user_data': {'dob': '1962-08-05 00:00:00', 'state': 'Alaska', 'age': 56, 'statecode': 'AK'}}, {'User': 'tpkn1422', 'Review': 'Love how fine it is. Does well if I use the entire side to draw a line along my lashes, but Im a cat eye kind of girl and this is horrible for cat eyes. It practically erases anything you try and re line and mine was dry after 3 uses! Honestly Ive tried almost every liner (except the tarte under the see liner) and my favorite is loreal from the drug store. Which is saying something because Im a sephora freak.', 'Score': 1, 'user_data': {'dob': '1975-08-02 00:00:00', 'state': 'Nevada', 'age': 43, 'statecode': 'NV'}}, {'User': 'lpmg3434', 'Review': 'I bought this on whim, hoping it would be of the same quality as the more expensive brands I usually buy. I didnt have high expectations and was kind of expecting it to fail---I was so wrong. This eyeliner is great and is currently my new favorite and has replaced my Kat Von D and Stila eyeliner purchases...and it saves me a bit of money, too! The color is very true black and extremely pigmented, the marker tip is nice and has not frayed on me (about 2 months of use). It doesnt smudge and it lasts all day. Definitely worth it!!', 'Score': 2, 'user_data': {'dob': '1999-07-27 00:00:00', 'state': 'Kansas', 'age': 19, 'statecode': 'KS'}}, {'User': 'afyr4422', 'Review': 'Easy to use, especially for those who do not know how to apply. Stay all day and it is easy to remove. love it!', 'Score': 3, 'user_data': {'dob': '1955-08-07 00:00:00', 'state': 'Indiana', 'age': 63, 'statecode': 'IN'}}, {'User': 'njwk2311', 'Review': 'Really like the color, and ease of use. It lasts all day and comes of fairly easy with makeup remover. Only complaint is the felt tip will start to wear out over time.', 'Score': 1, 'user_data': {'dob': '1959-08-06 00:00:00', 'state': 'Oklahoma', 'age': 59, 'statecode': 'OK'}}, {'User': 'yjpu4313', 'Review': 'As someone who is not always the best and making eyeliner match, this liner easier to use than others, and is certainly controllable for an eyeliner novices hand. I find with any felt tip eyeliner, the product does not go on as dark as I would like it to. In my experience, it takes a few passes to get that deep black look, but thats to be expected with any felt tip liner. Its a good, easy-to-use product and is definitely worth the price.', 'Score': 1, 'user_data': {'dob': '1955-08-07 00:00:00', 'state': 'Puerto Rico', 'age': 63, 'statecode': 'PR'}}]

description: This Hoover® vacuum features dual-stage cyclonic dirt separation technology, which separates clean air from dirt particles. There’s no loss of suction and you’ll get both cleaner carpets and air.   exclusive WindTunnel 2 technology includes crevice tool and dusting brush also includes HEPA media filter and reusable easy-rinse filter turbo tool cleans furniture and stairs 8' hose and 25' cord stretch hose for extended cleaning reach powerful, durable 12-amp motor Heavy-duty ABS plastic/rubber/metal. Reviews: [{'User': 'tsnz1243', 'Review': '1) the hose is TOO short. its a stretch to clean in my vehicle or behind furniture. you have a 2 reach. you cant pull it or it will break2) there is a loud humming/whistling noise that started two weeks after purchase. Reviews: [{'User': 'iato3142', 'Review': 'My MIL purchased this group for my newborn son in late 2009. Luckily, at that time Rockland offered a Coffee matching Toy Chest alongside the trio. She also purchased the matching conversion rails at the same time in case of any future discontinuation. My son, Rex, will be 7 this year and after all this time (and 4 residency moves!) THIS SET IS AMAZING STILL! Yes, initially it must be assembled.... but when it came to the safety of my newborn, I personally felt MORE comfortable knowing I would assemble it with much more attention to detail than a rushed-preassemble-factory! Other than the dresser & chest of drawers backing which is wood composite, the set IS solid wood. Depending on how its treated, wood does scratch... its not a bar of gold after all. If you have this set, try alternating or flipping the drawer panels for leveling out any use over time! Plus, Im very consistent in care when it comes to pledge-ing wood furniture but thats also because I understand the fact that it is meant to convert from crib, to toddler, to daybed, to eventually the full size bed; its supposed to maintain til then! name_title: Deborah Lippmann All About That Base CC Base Coat
description: What it is:A multitasking CC formula that provides 10 nail treatment benefits and immediate nail-perfecting coverage in one.What it does:This CC nail treatment is formulated with a special hydrating complex infused with panthenol, which helps to moisturize, strengthen, and protect the look of nails while treatment correctors assist with concealing imperfections, brightening, priming, and filling in ridges for a smooth and matte, flawless-looking finish with improved wear. This multipurpose polish can be used as a base coat with one coat, or apply two coats for a matte, modern look.What it is formulated WITHOUT:- Parabens- SulfatesWhat else you need to know:This product is a five-free formulation and is not tested on animals. It does not contain formaldehyde, formaldehyde resin, toluene, dbp (dibutyl phthlate), or camphor.Deborah was inspired by the continuing success of BBs and CC creams in the beauty world. She believes that nails are like skin and must tended to with the same care. This product offers what her brand excels at: catwalk inspired colors and cutting-edge care.Suggested Usage:-Apply one thin coat to bare nails and then apply two coats of lacquer. -Apply two or more coats to use alone for a modern, matte look. Precautions:-Warning: flammable. Avoid heat or flame.Ingredients​Ethyl Acetate, Butyl Acetate, Isopropyl Alcohol, Adipic Acid/Neopentyl Glycol/Trimellitic Anhydride Copolymer, Nitrocellulose, Talc, Triphenyl Phosphate, Cellulose, Hydrated Silica, Trimethyl Pentanyl Diisobutyrate, Stearalkonium Bentonite, Tosylamide/Epoxy Resin, Benzophenone-1, Diacetone Alcohol, Citric Acid, Sucrose Acetate Isobutyrate, Dimethicone, Biotin, Water/Aqua/Eau, Camellia Oleifera Leaf Extract, Caprylic/Capric/Succinic Triglyceride, Aucoumea Klaineana Resin Extract, Saccharide Isomerate, Cocos Nucifera (Coconut) Oil, Butylene Glycol, Macrocystis Pyrifera Extract, Beta-Carotene, Retinyl Palmitate, Ascorbic Acid, Tocopheryl Acetate, Panthenol, Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Iron Oxides (CI 77491), Yellow 5 Lake (CI 19140).
Reviews: [{'User': 'ztsh1341', 'Review': 'When the base coat is applied it dries so quickly that getting an even coat is difficult. It dries a textured satin/matte finish with a beige colour. Since if you brush more than one stroke it leaves bumpy streaks, putting polish over it does not look even. I tested this base coat at the same time against other base coats: Butter London Flawless Basecoat, Girly Bits Smooth Move, and A England The Knight. The Deborah Lippmann CC Base started chipping and flaking the first (< 24 hours) and the most. This was the most expensive base coat and performed poorly on application and chipping. All the nail treatment benefits (did not test long enough to comment on treatment) arent worth it if the polish does not stay on. This product was returned.', 'Score': 1, 'user_data': {'dob': '1997-07-27 00:00:00', 'state': 'Vermont', 'age': 21, 'statecode': 'VT'}}, {'User': 'nrhk4421', 'Review': 'This was just kinda meh. I got it on sale and I wish I could take it back. Its a little too pigmented to be a base coat, imo. If your nails have a lot of ridges and then you follow it with a light color or sheer shade, its not going to look good.', 'Score': 1, 'user_data': {'dob': '1960-08-05 00:00:00', 'state': 'Pennsylvania', 'age': 58, 'statecode': 'PA'}}, {'User': 'ucgq2122', 'Review': 'I tend to have ridges in my nails but with regular usage of this treatment the ridges are hardly visible.', 'Score': 2, 'user_data': {'dob': '1995-07-28 00:00:00', 'state': 'Louisiana', 'age': 23, 'statecode': 'LA'}}, {'User': 'hzbv1434', 'Review': 'This is one of my all time favorite base coats. And because of the nail health benefits, I feel this helps protect my nails and keeps them in good condition. One of my favorite combinations with this base coat is the Nails Inc Gel polish or the Butter London Gel polish with the Manicure Booster sealer as a top coat. My manicure will be perfect for 5 days which never happens! I also run this base coat along the tips of my nails to prevent chipping. description: Our cotton duck thermal roman shade is the perfect, stylish solution for reducing energy costs.   100% cotton duck fabric is backed with insulating thermal acrylic foam unique design folds neatly as shade is raised auto-locking pull cord protect your home from the heat and cold white backing faces outside for uniform exterior appearance optional 7" valance Sold individually. Imported.  *Cost savings represent the relative cost of heating or cooling an area to account for heat lost or gained through a window. Savings reflect comparison to a bare single-pane window. Energy Savings logo developed by JCPenney for exclusive use. Energy Savings testing conducted by an independent third-party laboratory.

Unfortunately, 2 of the 4 shades did not lock in place properly when the shade was pulled up, and one side fell. After trying numerous times to get the locking mechanism to stick, I finally had to take them both down and return them. I returned them to JC Penney catalog department and ordered 2 more. They arrived and I had no problem with either one. And because I liked them so much, I ordered 6 more - 4 for my bedroom windows and 2 for my bathroom windows. They arrived on time and we hung all 6. ENERGY STAR® qualified 48 dBA with status indicator on the door full-extension, smooth glide upper rack that fully extends on ball bearings easy touch adjustable upper rack with 2 Stem Safe shelves that can move moved 2 inches up or down to accommodate tall glassware and 10½" plates lower rack with adjustable tines and Wash Your Way customizable rack 3-piece silverware basket and dedicated silverware jets wash zones allow you to wash a true half-load in either the upper or lower rack with the same cycles available on a full wash 3-digit countdown display with delay start sanitize option (NSF residential) reduces 99.999% of bacteria found on dishes rinse aid indicator light signals when rinse aid is low Steam PreWash loosens tough soils so you don't have to pre-rinse Piranha™ hard food disposer with removable filter pulverizes food particles to prevent clogging 65% more wash power compared to other GE models Floor Protect with Alert Technology easily detects uncommon leaks hidden vent with fan that circulates air to remove moisture
Reviews: [{'User': 'gaqt1134', 'Review': 'I bought this dishwasher to replace a 15 year-old GE dishwasher that is the best appliance I ever had. The pluses are that it is very attractive and super quiet. The minuses are that Im not sure yet how much I like the SS interior. It is very dark to see inside. This seems to have really compromised the rinse agent compartment for which the holes are tiny, for one, to pour the rinse agent into and its impossible to read the labeling without getting really close. The biggest problem, however, is that the plastic peep hole that turns blue when filled is impossible to see in the dark interior. This design oversight is a nuisance and why I gave the machine 4 and not 5 stars. Finally, I ran the machine using the maximum settings due to the amount of dirty pots and pans and it took all evening. Its run time is much longer than any dishwasher Ive ever had before. Knowing these things I might have reconsidered the purchase.', 'Score': 2, 'user_data': {'dob': '1967-08-04 00:00:00', 'state': 'Mississippi', 'age': 51, 'statecode': 'MS'}}, {'User': 'bupj3112', 'Review': 'Got a very good deal on the pricing; machine is very quiet and easy to use. Reviews: [{'User': 'fncd4133', 'Review': 'This chair is not only classically stylish but also well-made and extremely comfy. I am 58 and it suits me perfectly for nursing. name_title: Perfect Formula Neutral Gel Coat Color
description: What it is:A nail strengthening nail polish with a neutral hue. What it does:Neutral Gel Coat Color is formulated to create a thick protein-rich coating that instantly strengthens, seals, and protects nails so they can grow strong and healthyno base coat or top coat necessary. It's ideal for all nail types, and it strengthens brittle nails, weak nails, splitting and peeling nails, and even nails damaged by salon acrylic or gel. Enriched with keratin, the main protein of the nail, this nail polish is an all-in-one base coat, nail color, top coat, and strengthener. What else you need to know:Perfect Formula Neutral Gel Coat Color removes easily with nail polish remover.Precautions:-Keep away from heat and flame. -Keep out of the reach of children.Size:0.60 ozIngredients:​ Ethyl Acetate, Butyl Acetate, Phthalic Anhydride/Trimellitic Anhydride/Glycols Copolymer, Nitrocellulose, Isopropyl Alcohol, Acetyl Tributyl Citrate, Tosylamide/Formaldehyde Resin, Silica Dimethyl Silylate, Camphor, Cyclotetrasiloxane, Etocrylene, Disodium Distyrylbiphenyl Disulfonate, Hydrolyzed Keratin, Calcium Pantothenate, May Contain: Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), D&C Red No. 6 (CI 15850), D&C Red No. 34 (CI 15880), D&C Yellow No. 5 (CI 19140), Ferric Ferrocyanide (CI 77510), Iron Oxides (CI 77491), Bismuth Oxychloride (CI 77163), Mica (CI 77019).

Reviews: [{'User': 'blmw2443', 'Review': 'This dress is so cute. I ordered it online, because the selection for 2P is always very poor in the store. The fabric is very soft, and has some stretch to it. The dress looks very elegant and the red belt line make it look very interesting and energetic. The fit is true to size. On the inside is has a lining from neck to chest. I chose to wear a slip with it, just to ensure it moves smoothly and is not transparent. name_title: Kartoum Washable Rectangular Rug
description: Add color and warmth to any room with these rugs featuring a Jacobean-inspired print. The muted tones will go beautifully with almost any decor.   highly durable nylon slip-resistant latex back crafted and printed in America ¼" pile height; ½" overall thickness Stain Resistant: Yes Fade Resistant: Yes Slip Resistant: Yes Rug Backing: Latex Fire Retardant: Yes Rug Pad Recommended: No, the latex backing provides slip resistance and protection for underlying floors. Use: Indoor Care Instructions: Washable Origin: Made in America
Reviews: [{'User': 'aeyn4332', 'Review': 'I had been seeking a reasonably priced. fully synthetic area rug with an Oriental pattern for several months and had found some I liked, but later found the backing was typically jute, which is organic and needs special care. As a pet owner, I wanted something that looked good and was easy to clean; synthetic fibers are hard to stain. The backing on this rug is latex, which is washable and does not slip on the floor. I was also looking for a color scheme of blues, creams and muted greens and finally found it in the Blue Kartoum Rug. Best of all, it was on sale! I ordered a 5 x 8 area rug and a matching smaller one. When it arrived, I was somewhat dismayed that the brown was so prominent and the blue less so. In the photo, it appears to have a really wide blue border, but in the sizes I got, it is not as wide and the cream that edges the rug minimizes it more. As I liked the other features of the rug I decided to keep it for a few days and see if it grew on me-it did. Actually, the dark pattern is not all brown, but dark green with dark beige patterns intermixed. The blue band is more of a teal with green, off white and tan designs scattered throughout. Interestingly, there is also a paler, medium blue design interspersed on the off white background in the middle of the rug and that helps to balance the brown. It is really an interesting pattern and it will certain help to disguise any dirt. As for being easy care, one of my cats decided to christen it with its breakfast, I wiped it up and squirted some Res*lve type rug cleaner on it and pouf, it was gone! The rug can be washed in a washing machine if you have a smaller size or a professional sized washer. When mine needs it, I plan to drag it out on the deck, blast it with the hose and some soap, then hang it out to dry. Its not super thick so it should be easy to do. (The 5 x 8 weighs 15 lbs.) The weave is dense, and it is soft underfoot; the way the pattern blends smoothly together makes it looks like a much more expensive rug. However, if you want a super thick pile this will not be up to your standards, although you could get a pad to increase the thickness. All in all, I feel like this rug is quite a bargain! (I did omit one star because I wish there had been a bit more blue and less brown. What can I say, I love blue!)', 'Score': 1, 'user_data': {'dob': '1998-07-27 00:00:00', 'state': 'Iowa', 'age': 20, 'statecode': 'IA'}}, {'User': 'dtjt4314', 'Review': 'using two of these in kitchen...one in front of sink; otherin front of frige..............perfect.....no moving orcatching shoes on edges', 'Score': 2, 'user_data': {'dob': '1992-07-28 00:00:00', 'state': 'Wyoming', 'age': 26, 'statecode': 'WY'}}, {'User': 'rukx3424', 'Review': 'This is a great rug and I love that it is washable.', 'Score': 1, 'user_data': {'dob': '1990-07-29 00:00:00', 'state': 'California', 'age': 28, 'statecode': 'CA'}}]
